==Hungarian==
===Etymology===
From the same Uralic root *''e'' as Finnish [[että]] and Estonian [[et#Estonian|et]]
===Demonstrative pronoun===
'''ez'''

# [[this]] (used as a pronoun, that is, instead of a noun phrase)

===Demonstrative determiner===
'''ez'''

# [[this]] (used before a noun phrase with a definite article)

===Quotations===

#'''1836''': Vörösmarty Mihály, Szózat
#: Ez a föld, melyen annyiszor <br> Apáid vére folyt; <br> Ez, melyhez minden szent nevet <br> Egy ezredév csatolt.
#::(The first occasion shows '''ez''' az a determiner, the second as a pronoun)

